summary: Hey I'm new to Killing Eve (kinda...I'm on my 3rd rewatch lol) but I'm trying to dip my toes in the fandom bc it seems so...
question: Hey I'm new to Killing Eve (kinda...I'm on my 3rd rewatch lol) but I'm trying to dip my toes in the fandom bc it seems so awesome. You guys are so creative and imaginative and everyone has crazy amazing fresh theories about the characters and I love it. Coming from an old, bitter fandom it's refreshing 👌 The love is real here
answer:
a big killing eve welcome to you!!

i love this fandom so much i have made so many friends because people are incredibly kind and love to share theories and just talk about the show. it’s truly an amazing place.

i was talking with a friend, and we decided killing eve is part of the renaissance of fandom tumblr. it’s such a supportive community.

i lost a lot of faith when lexa died. i got really out of it, but i watched this show and knew it was something special.

excited to ride this wave out through season 2 and beyond!!

summary: “Every day we suppress our emotions, we don’t want to show our emotions, we might feel embarrassed about something and we try...
caption:
“Every day we suppress our emotions, we don’t want to show our emotions, we might feel embarrassed about something and we try and hide it. What I love about going into filming is I could be dancing all day, I could be crying, I could be laughing; everything is about feeling.”

Jodie Comer born March 11th, 1993.
